title: NewsReporterStory1
tags:
position: 169,38
---
News Reporter Ghost: O-oh! I don't think we've met yet... but I don't think you want to.
News Reporter Ghost: I'm News Reporter Ghost, but I don't really run news stories or interviews anymore.
News Reporter Ghost: While you're here, I want to thank you for your service.
News Reporter Ghost: If I still had a news station, I'd continuously advertise you. You've made a good impact on the ghosts, as far as I've seen, which... is more than I have done...
News Reporter Ghost: What? You want to know... my story?
News Reporter Ghost: I thought it was well known enough, but... you're the first ghost to ask me for my perspective directly from me.
News Reporter Ghost: Where do I start?
News Reporter Ghost: When I was but a small boy, I dreamed of giving every story light within the community.
News Reporter Ghost: I watched my friends' stories get trashed and erased, and I wanted to make an impact.
News Reporter Ghost: So, I continued that pipe dream, went to a couple universities, and became a pretty famous news reporter.
News Reporter Ghost: The headlines I released, the stories I told... they were for the whole world to see every morning at 11 and every evening at 6.
News Reporter Ghost: It was good. I felt like I could make a difference, like I could change the world... and then the story came.
News Reporter Ghost: I... I don't think I'm ready to tell you the rest of the pain yet.
News Reporter Ghost: I'm sorry, but I need a bit of time. I've never communicated this to someone and it's... hard.
News Reporter Ghost: I'll fill you in... next time.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
===

title: NewsReporterStory2
tags:
position: 169,38
---
News Reporter Ghost: Sigh... I need to get this off my chest before it kills me.
News Reporter Ghost: Anyway... I had previously described my excitement to change the world.
News Reporter Ghost: One fateful day, I had to research a court trial about a serial killer who hurt so many innocent people.
News Reporter Ghost: One of those people... let's just say I had personal stakes in this trial. So, when a person was brought to light, I immediately accused them... on live television.
News Reporter Ghost: You know how the media is - it's so easy to twist and spin into your own narrative, and because I was so well-known, it became other people's narratives, too.
News Reporter Ghost: The person was hated across the world, and the trial was an easy one to predict with my hands in it.
News Reporter Ghost: I continued to release press after press against them, consumed with a desire to prove the world that I was right... but I was really just trying to justify condemning a person to myself.
News Reporter Ghost: Lawyer Ghost found me before the trial and chatted with me - well, chatted is a very loose word.
News Reporter Ghost: He ended up punching me in the eye, and I guess it stuck with me.
News Reporter Ghost: He left me some evidence, too, and it showed what I had feared to be true.
News Reporter Ghost: The person was innocent - they were a scapegoat to an undercover terrorist organization.
News Reporter Ghost: How could I have been so wrong?
News Reporter Ghost: I wanted to share everyone's stories to the world, but I chose my own story, my own narrative, over them in the end.
News Reporter Ghost: Eventually, I turned myself in, spent some time in prison, and let my successor tell the story of how I was wrong.
News Reporter Ghost: It still haunts me to this day... as much as a memory can haunt a ghost.
News Reporter Ghost: You see why it was so hard to tell you this?
News Reporter Ghost: I made an impact on the world that I couldn't fix or erase... and now I'm left to deal with it alone, because how could anyone love me or care for me after all I've done?
News Reporter Ghost: I... oh, this ripped the memories out of my chest.
News Reporter Ghost: I'll see you... next time.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
===

